HEADWORD: Maigre
<hw>Mai"gre</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Meager</er>.]</ety> <def>Belonging to a fast day or fast; <as>as, a
<ex>maigre</ex> day</as>.</def> <rj><au>Walpole.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Maigre food</b></col> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld>, <cd>food
allowed to be eaten on fast days.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

